      • parseTag

        public static java.lang.String parseTag(TimeRefTag t1)
        This method returns the tag in String format to prevent loss of resolution. Double floating point precision is only 15 digits, hence the tag String should NOT be parsed directly as double, rather split into seconds and fractions parts and read separately. NOTE: This method doesn't manipulate the tag value (e.g. doesn't add/subtract correction errors and/or base seconds, all calculations have to be done prior to calling this method)
        Parameters:
        t1 -
        Returns:
        tag value in String format.

      • applyErrorCorrection

        public static void applyErrorCorrection(TimeRefTag tag,
                                        double errCorrection)
        Apply error correction to time tag. Error correction value is calculated from 1pps (GPS) signal measured on ARM input.
        Parameters:
        tag - tag object
        errCorrection - error correction value.
